  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently the notifier doesn't get syncing information from the sync manager. When no peers are connected, the notifier thinks we are syncing, when we are actually `stalled`. \r\n\r\nUnder the hood there are four kinds of sync state:\r\n- Stalled - No peers, no way to progress\r\n- Finalized - We are syncing a finalized chain to reach a peers known finalized slot\r\n- Head - We are syncing head chains to reach a peers head slot\r\n- Regular - We are fully synced (up to a tolerance), and we do block parent lookups from peers when we see unknown blocks. \r\n\r\nAt a very minimum the notifier should know about Stalled, and we should decide whether the other states should be relayed to the user",
